,Recommended,247580,10180923,"Posted: 20 May, 2014",all,georgetsa93,"This review is for the 2D casual action rpg game,originally released for ios and android enabled devices,Magicka: Wizards of the Square Tablet.The game was developed by Ludosity and published by Paradox Interactive in 2012 and on 31/10 2013 on Steam.PlotSince this game was ported from mobile and tablet devices the storyline is fairly simple and the plot is fast paced,yet innovative.Because this game is so small i will not spoil you the fun from discovering the magicks and secrets of Asgard.GameplayThe game utilizes the same old Magicka's element combination system in order to create powerful Magicks.Available elements are:Earth,Fire,Ice,Lightning,Water,Shield,and Healing.Those elements can be used offencively or defencively.They can be used individually and can be empowered by selecting the same element as much as four times,increasing it's intensity,or they can be combined in order to create incredible spells,called Magicks.Pros+Fast paced+Sharp cartoon visuals+Simple gameplay and storyline+Advanced fighting combinatons possible+Cross platform multyplayerCons-A few crashes-Unlockables already unlockedRecapNice,fun little game with sharp cartoon graphics and increasing difficulty.What more can you ask for?"
